Conclusion

VLAN hopping exploits weaknesses in switch configurations. Switch spoofing tricks a switch into opening a trunk link, while double tagging exploits VLAN tag processing. Proper security measures, such as disabling auto-trunking and enforcing VLAN tagging rules, can prevent these attacks. ğŸš€
